title: FOIL Method
text: The F stands for First, where we multiply the first component of each terms first. $$x^2 x$$

title: FOIL Method
text: The O stands for Outer, where we multiply the first component of the second term with the $$\frac{second}{outer}$$ component of the second term. $$x^2 \left(-8\right)$$

title: FOIL Method
text: The I stands for Inner, where we multiply the inner components. $$6x$$

title: FOIL Method
text: The L stands for Last, where we multiply the last component of each terms. $$6\left(-8\right)$$
